cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new approach to learning compact embeddings for large-vocab sparse features in recommender systems. It also involves extensive experiments to evaluate the proposed approach's performance on three recommendation tasks and two datasets. 

It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as recommender systems are often used in information retrieval applications. 

Furthermore, it could be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks in recommender systems. 

It may also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as recommender systems can be used in image and video recommendation applications. 

Finally, it could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing a new approach to improve recommendation performance with compact model sizes.
